bugle /ˈbjuːɡəl/

(bugles) 

1. N-COUNT A bugle is a simple brass musical instrument that looks like a small trumpet. Bugles are often used in the army to announce when activities such as meals are about to begin. 军号 

2. V to play or sound (on) a bugle 吹军号 

3. N any of several Eurasian plants of the genus Ajuga , esp A. reptans , having small blue or white flowers: family Lamiaceae (labiates) 筋骨草 (Also called bugleweed)  →  see also ground pine 

4. N a tubular glass or plastic bead sewn onto clothes for decoration 圆管状饰珠

